How to check if ith bit is set or not of number num i.e. (num & 1<<(i-1))

 We have to check if ith bit is set or not

 Step 1 : Take number 1 
 Step 2 : Left shift this to i-1 times so the number becomes 10000 (like this)
 Step 3 : DO Bitwise And  with num to check if the ith bit is set or not

 For Example : 
      Let's Have number 9 
	  Its Binary representation is 1001
	  if we have to check is 4th bit

	  According to steps take 1 and left shift it 3 times so Number is 1000
	  Now 
	   1001
	&1000
	Results 1000 that is not zero which means that 4th bit is set.

