# Approach
at first we took 3 variable 'low','high','mid'. 'Low' set at first ,'high' set at last of the index .
then we used a while loop until low becomes 'equal' of high.
then we calculated the mid;

we checked if our mid is Bad .if then we will check the previous(mid-1) value is good or not .if previous is good then the bad starts from mid; ----------so return mid 
for example [low(good),mid-1(good),mid(bad),#(bad),high(bad)]


if mid is bad but the previous one(mid-1) is also bad 
for example [low(good),mid-1(bad),mid(bad),#(bad),high(bad)]
then we will shift our high value to mid-1 position;


if mid is not bad
for example [low(good),mid-1(good),mid(good),#(bad),high(bad)]
then our 'low' will be 'mid+1'.because we dont have to check till mid because till mid is all good;




