The problem asks for the **first occurrence** of the bad version, that is the **lower bound** of the bad version.
**Approach -
1. We will search whether the mid is bad or good.
2. If the mid version is bad, we will further check if it is the first bad version.
3. If it is the first bad version we will simply return the mid.
4. If it is not the first bad version we can simply call for (r=mid-1), i.e; the lower or first half.
5. If the mid version is good then it is clear that, all versions before it will also be good and we will search for the bad version in the upper or greater half, i.e; l = mid + 1.****

 ****This is simple implementation of finding first occurrence of an element in a sorted array. 


**CODE:**
```
// The API isBadVersion is defined for you.
// bool isBadVersion(int version);

class Solution
{
    public:
        int firstBadVersion(int n)
        {
            int l = 1, r = n;
            while (l <= r)
            {
                int mid = l + (r - l) / 2;
                if (isBadVersion(mid))
                {
                    if (mid != 1 and isBadVersion(mid - 1))
                    {
                        r = mid - 1;
                    }
                    else
                    {
                        return mid;
                    }
                }
                else
                {
                    l = mid + 1;
                }
            }
            return r;
        }
};
```

