solutions.content:
To find the kth smallest is to the find the first one which is >= kth smallest, that is, the first one which has >= k non-bigger elements. We could apply lower-bound Binary Search among [min, max] for min is the topleft cell while max is the bottom right cell.

In the utility method `countNonBigger`, we can make use of the sorting feature of the matrix. That is, if we start at the bottomleft, for the bigger, we can only move right, for the smaller, we can only move up, and accumulate the number of elements upon the cell (inclusive) within the same column.
****
```
    public int kthSmallest(int[][] matrix, int k) {
        int n = matrix.length, lo = matrix[0][0], hi = matrix[n - 1][n - 1];

        while (lo <= hi) {
            int mi = lo + ((hi - lo) >> 1);
            int count = countNonBigger(mi, matrix);
            if (count < k) {
                lo = mi + 1;
            } else {
                hi = mi - 1;
            }
        }

        return lo;
    }

    private static int countNonBigger(int target, int[][] matrix) {
        int n = matrix.length, i = n - 1, j = 0, cnt = 0;
        while (i >= 0 && j < n) {
            if (matrix[i][j] > target) {
                i--;
            } else {
                cnt += i + 1;
                j++;
            }
        }

        return cnt;
    }
