solutions.content:
**1. MaxHeap**
O(n^2log(k)). This does not use the fact that the matrix is sorted.
```
 public int kthSmallest(int[][] matrix, int k) {
        Queue<Integer> pq=new PriorityQueue<>((a,b)->b-a);  
        for(int[] r:matrix)
            for(int n:r) {
                pq.add(n);
                if(pq.size()>k) pq.poll();
            }
        return pq.peek();
    }
```
**2. Merge k sorted lists**
O(min(n,k)+klog(min(n,k))). Build heap from array is linear. You can use make_heap in c++. In java, adding each element to priority queue is nlogn. This approach uses the fact that the first row is sorted and the columns are sorted. So something is still missing.
```
	public int kthSmallest(int[][] matrix, int k) {
        Queue<int[]> pq=new PriorityQueue<>((a,b)->a[0]-b[0]);  
        for(int i=0;i<Math.min(matrix[0].length,k);i++)
            pq.add(new int[]{matrix[0][i],0,i}); 
        for(int i=1;i<k;i++) {
            int[] arr=pq.poll(); 
            if(arr[1]<matrix.length-1) {
                pq.add(new int[]{matrix[arr[1]+1][arr[2]],arr[1]+1,arr[2]});  
            }
        }
        return pq.peek()[0];
    }
```
**3. Binary search** 
Time complexity nlog(max-min). It is better than #2 because k could be n^2 in the worst case.
1) Loop invariance
For x<l, rank(x)<k, for x>=r, rank(x)>=k
So when l==r, x is the smallest number with rank k.
2) Why l exists in the matirx in the end.
Most binary search we can check target==mid during the search and return. But this one we cannot because the first mid we find with rank k might not exist in the matrix. Continuing the binary search finds the smallest number with rank k. For example, rank(l-1)=k-1 and rank(l)=k. If l is not in the matrix, then rank(l-1)=rank(l). So the smallest number that ranks k in the matrix must exist in the matrix.
3) getRank is same as 240. Search a 2D Matrix II. Now all the given conditions are used.
```
public int kthSmallest(int[][] matrix, int k) {
        int l=matrix[0][0], r=matrix[matrix.length-1][matrix[0].length-1];
        while(l<r) {
            int mid=(l+r)/2;
            int rank=getRank(mid,matrix);
            if(rank<k) l=mid+1;
            else r=mid;
        }
        return r;
    }
    private int getRank(int num, int[][] matrix) {
        int rank=0, i=0, j=matrix[0].length-1;
        while(i<matrix.length && j>=0) {
            if(matrix[i][j]<=num) {
                rank+=j+1;
                i++;
            } else j--;
        }
        return rank;
    }
```

