**Approach1: Brute Force**
Put all elements in an array of size n^2. Sort it and return kth element in the array.
TC: (n^2 logn) [Sorting]
SC: (n^2)

**Approach2: Using Heap.**
Build heap of n elements and perform min heapify k times. Put all the values in first row in a min heap. Now, extract the min element and put the greater value (element present in same column and next row) in the heap. We'll do this k times. And, the element extracted from heap kth time will be the answer. 

TC: O(n + klogn) [Build heap of n elements, and perform min heapify operation k times]
SC: O(n) [Heap of size n]

```
class Solution {
public:
    int kthSmallest(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int k) {
        int val;
        priority_queue<pair<int, pair<int,int>>, vector<pair<int, pair<int,int>>>, greater<pair<int, pair<int,int>>>> pq;

        for(int j=0;j<matrix.size();j++) 
            pq.push({matrix[0][j], {0, j}});

        for(int i=0;i<k;i++) {
            int x, y;
            val = pq.top().first;
            x = pq.top().second.first;
            y = pq.top().second.second;
            pq.pop();

            if(x < matrix.size()-1)
                pq.push({matrix[x+1][y], {x+1, y}});
        }
        return val;
    }
};
```

**Approach3: Binary Search**
The ans will lie between marix[0][0] & matrix[n-1][n-1]. Do binary search on this range. For every mid value, we find the number of elements (say, count) that are lesser or equal to that value, and search in left or right half accordingly.

TC: O(log(y-x) * nlogn) where y and x are largest and smallest elements in matrix [Binary search, and find count]
SC: O(1)

```
class Solution {
public:
    int kthSmallest(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int k) {
        int n = matrix.size(), l = matrix[0][0], r = matrix[n-1][n-1];
        while(l <= r) {
            int mid = (l + r)/2;
            int count = smallerOrEqualElements(matrix, mid);
            if(count >= k)
                r = mid - 1;
            else 
                l = mid + 1;
        }
        return l;
    }

    int smallerOrEqualElements(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int val) {
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<matrix.size();i++) { //Check number of smaller or equal elements for each row
            if(val < matrix[i][0])
                return ans;
            ans += upper_bound(matrix[i].begin(), matrix[i].end(), val) - matrix[i].begin();
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```


