solutions.content:
-> The range of our ans lies within the minimum and maximum of given matrix.
-> Our answer is the kth smallest number in matrix, which means count of numbers smaller than or equal to answer will be greater than or equal to k . 
		*Why greater than or equal to and not equal to ?*
		*-> Because we can have duplicate numbers in our matrix.*

Let's say we have a function check(x) which returns true if count of numbers smaller than or equal to x (in matrix) is greater than or equal to k, otherwise returns false.

-> **check(x) will be true for our answer (kth smallest number) and any number greater than our answer.**

	i.e check(x) is a **monotonic function**, which can be represented as : - 
	FFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF**T**TTTTTTTTTTT
	and the smallest x for which check(x) returns T (true) is our required answer (kth smallest number in matrix).

-> We can use binary search to find our answer (x, s.t check(x)==true and check(x-1)==false)
-> range for our binary search will be [min(matrix), max(matrix]
-> At each step of binary search, we calculate the mid element and find where check(mid) is true false
-> check(mid) can be computed in O(nlogn) time using upper_bound on each row of matrix
-> if check(mid) is true then we store it in our answer variable and update our range :  end = mid-1
-> if check(mid) is false then we do not store it and update our range : start = mid+1
after the complete iteration of binary search answer variable will store kth smallest number.
**Code **

```
class Solution {
public:
    bool check(vector<vector<int>>& matrix,int mid,int k){
        int ans = 0;
        for(int i=0;i<matrix.size();++i){
            ans+=upper_bound(matrix[i].begin(),matrix[i].end(),mid) - matrix[i].begin();
        }
        return (ans>=k);
    }
    int kthSmallest(vector<vector<int>>& matrix, int k) {
        int n = matrix.size();
		// start : starting point our current range for binary search
        int start = matrix[0][0], end = matrix[n-1][n-1];

		// ans variable will store kth smallest number
        int ans;
        while(end>=start){
            int mid = start + (end-start)/2;
            if(check(matrix,mid,k)){
			// mid is a probable answer store it and look for numbers left to it
			// we want to find smallest x s.t check(x)==true
                ans = mid;
                end = mid-1;
            }
            else{
			// ans lies to right of mid
                start = mid + 1;
            }
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

