/**
 * @param {number[][]} matrix
 * @param {number} k
 * @return {number}
 */
var kthSmallest = function(matrix, k) {
    return matrix.flat().sort((a, b) => a - b)[k - 1];
};
```
The `flat()` function basically allows you to create a new array with all sub-array elements concatenated together upto a certain depth.

By flattening the matrix, we get a single array with all it's elements. Since it is not necessary that the new array has all elements sorted given that only the sub-array and their elements were sorted initially, we need to sort the new array too. Then we return the **(k - 1)th** element in the sorted array.

