```
The idea is to keep all values in heap, if heap size exceeds k, 
then remove one element from heap.
At last, return peek number. that is the kth smallest number.

Note:- This is one of the accepted solutions, but not the best one. 

Time: O(N * N * logN)
Space: O(k)
```
```

class Solution {
    public int kthSmallest(int[][] M, int k) {
        PriorityQueue<Integer> heap = new PriorityQueue<>((a, b) -> b - a);
        for(int[] R : M){
            for(int a : R){
                heap.add(a);
                if(heap.size() > k)
                    heap.poll();
            }
        }
        return heap.peek();
    }
}
```

