This is a variant of [240. Search a 2D Matrix II](https://leetcode.com/problems/search-a-2d-matrix-ii/). The key point is that for given value ```mid```, it takes only ```O(n)``` times (because it is proprotional to the length of the diagonal) to determine how many elements less than ```mid```. Bearing this in mind, one should be able to make the concept into a code:
```
def kthSmallest(self, matrix, k):
        n = len(matrix)
        lo, hi = matrix[0][0], matrix[-1][-1]

        while lo < hi:
            mid = (lo+hi) // 2

			# saddleback search
            p, q, c = n-1, 0, 0 #(p,q) moving point, c: count
            while 0<=p and q < n:
                if matrix[p][q] > mid:
                    p -= 1
                else:
                    c += p + 1 # update number of elm < mid; 1 is bec p being an ind
                    q += 1

            # binary search
            if c < k:
                lo = mid + 1
            else:
                hi = mid

        return lo
```

