# Approach
- Create a priority queue.
- Simply iterate through all the elements in the matrix:
  1) For each element, push it into the priority queue.
  2) If the size of the priority queue exceeds k, remove the largest element using q.pop().
- Retrun the top element of the priority queue, which is the kth smallest element.
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(Nlogk) where N is number of elements in matrix.
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(k)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
