solutions.content:
First straightforward answer is to use BFS. The time complexity will be around O(k) but we'll have to use some space(O(N^2)) to track visited cells. 
```
    private class Point {
        int x;
        int y;
        int val;
        public Point(int x, int y, int val) {
            this.x = x;
            this.y = y;
            this.val = val;
        }
    }

    public int kthSmallest(int[][] matrix, int k) {
        int n = matrix.length;
        PriorityQueue<Point> minHeap = new PriorityQueue<Point>((
            (p1, p2) -> p1.val - p2.val
        ));
        boolean[][] visited = new boolean[n][n];
        minHeap.add(new Point(0, 0, matrix[0][0]));
        visited[0][0] = true;
        while (!minHeap.isEmpty() && k > 1) {
            Point curr = minHeap.poll();
            int x = curr.x, y = curr.y;
            if (y + 1 < n && !visited[x][y + 1]) {
                minHeap.add(new Point(x, y + 1, matrix[x][y + 1]));
                visited[x][y + 1] = true;
            }
            if (x + 1 < n && !visited[x + 1][y]) {
                minHeap.add(new Point(x + 1, y, matrix[x + 1][y]));
                visited[x + 1][y] = true;
            }
            k--;
        }
        return minHeap.poll().val;
    }
```



Second solution is to binary search the answer. So the question breaks down to two parts, binary cut the answer range and try to determine the count. Because of it's sorted by rows and cols, we can easily make the count function O(N). So the time for this solution is O(NlogN).
```
    public int kthSmallest(int[][] matrix, int k) {
        int n = matrix.length;
        int l = matrix[0][0];
        int r = matrix[n - 1][n - 1];
        while (l < r) {
            int mid = l + (r - l) / 2;
            if (count(matrix, mid) < k) {
                l = mid + 1;
            } else {
                r = mid;
            }
        }
        return l;
    }

    // return the smaller or equal value count of target
    private int count(int[][] A, int target) {
        int n = A.length;
        int ans = 0;
        int j = n - 1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            while (j >= 0 && A[i][j] > target) j--;
            if (j == -1) break;
