------------
------------

***Solution - III (Further Space-Optimisation using custom hash)***

We don't need to store the entire strings in the hashmaps as we did above. We can convert the string to a hash value and store it as a integer. 

In this problem, since the max length of word/query is `7`, we won't see much benefits (in the best case, we are improving space for keys from **`7 bytes`** to **`4 bytes`** for int). But if the words are of larger size, it would be an much optimised approach.

```
string toLowercase(string &s){
	for(char& c : s) c = tolower(c);
	return s;
}
bool isVowel(char c){
	return c == 'a' || c == 'e' || c == 'i' || c == 'o' || c == 'u';
}
string maskVowel(string &s){
	for(char& c : s) if(isVowel(c)) c = '#';
	return s;
}
int hash(string s){
	long h = 0, mod = 1e9 + 7;
	for(char& c : s) h = (h * 101 + c) % mod;
	return h;
}
vector<string> spellchecker(vector<string>& wordlist, vector<string>& queries) {
	unordered_set<int> orig;
	unordered_map<int, string> lowered, vowelMasked;
	string tmp;
	for(vector<string>::reverse_iterator word = rbegin(wordlist); word != rend(wordlist); word++) 
		tmp = *word,orig.insert(hash(tmp)), lowered[hash(toLowercase(tmp))] = *word, vowelMasked[hash(maskVowel(tmp))] = *word;
	int h;
	for(string& q : queries)
		if(orig.count(hash(q))) continue;
		else if(lowered.count(h = hash(toLowercase(q)))) q = lowered[h];
		else if(vowelMasked.count(h = hash(maskVowel(q)))) q = vowelMasked[h];
		else q = "";
	return queries;
}
```

**Time Complexity :** **`O(N + Q)`**, where `N` is the sum of lengths of words in `wordlist` and `Q` is the sum of lengths of queries.
**Space Complexity :** **`O(N)`**, for storing in the hashmaps. Although, the space complexity is still the same, we have eliminated a good chunk of constant factor without any addition to time complexity.

Note that we would need to choose a good hash function. Luckily, the one I chose didn't give any collisions. For more robust solution, you would need to handle collision cases also.

