solutions.content:
Three types of query words:
1. The query is same as the word in the wordlist.
2. The query has the same letters and the same order, but has subtle different with the capitalization.
3. The query has similar letters. Only the vowels part are different with the word in the wordlist.

Iterate wordlist:
1. Add the word into `HashSet`.
2. Capitalize the word and add to the first `HashMap`.
3. Replace the vowels to `*` then add to the second `HashMap`. 

Since the question also noted that only return the first match, so only put the word into map when first meet.

Queries:

- For type 1 : Return the same word in the wordlist.
- For type 2 : Capitalize the query and return the word (all capitalize) from the first map.
- For type 3 : Replace the vowel part of the query (after capitalize), and return the word from the second map.
- For others: Return the empty string.

```
class Solution {
    public String[] spellchecker(String[] wordlist, String[] queries) {
        HashSet<String> same = new HashSet<String>();
        HashMap<String, String> caseInsensitive = new HashMap<String, String>();
        HashMap<String, String> vowelMap = new HashMap<String, String>();

        for (String word: wordlist) {
			same.add(word);
            String capital = word.toUpperCase();
            caseInsensitive.putIfAbsent(capital, word);
            vowelMap.putIfAbsent(replaceVowel(capital), word);
        }

        String[] res = new String[queries.length];
        for (int i = 0; i < queries.length; i++) {
            if (same.contains(queries[i])) {
                res[i] = queries[i];
                continue;
            }

            String cap = queries[i].toUpperCase(), vow = replaceVowel(cap);
            if (caseInsensitive.containsKey(cap)) {
                res[i] = caseInsensitive.get(cap);
            } else if (vowelMap.containsKey(vow)) {
                res[i] = vowelMap.get(vow);
            } else {
                res[i] = "";
            }
        }
        return res;

    }

    private String replaceVowel(String s) {
        char[] ch = s.toCharArray();
        for (int i = 0; i < ch.length; i++) {
            if (ch[i] == 'A' || ch[i] == 'E' || ch[i] == 'I' || ch[i] == 'O' || ch[i] == 'U')
                ch[i] = '*';
        }
        return new String(ch);
    }
}
```

