The solution is simple as follows:
1- Define the max and min range of Xs and Ys. 
2- Use Random double to get a random value. The popular formula to get a random double value between a range is : double randomValue = rangeMin + (rangeMax - rangeMin) * r.nextDouble();
However, since the rangeMin can be negative, I have changed it to
 rangeMax + (rangeMin-rangeMax) * r.nextDouble(); and simplified it as :
 x_min=-2*radius; x_max=radius+x_center;
 y_min=-2*radius; y_max=radius+y_center; 
 3- Now everytime you get a random X & Y, make sure the distance of the random point to the center is in the max range. The formula is:
  Distance =√(x2−centerX)^2+(y2−centerY)^2  which is equals to Radius^2=(x2−centerX)^2+(y2−centerY)^2
